HEADWORD: Gloppen
<hw>Glop"pen</hw> <pr>(gl⟦ocr⟧p"p⟦eit⟧n)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos>
<ety>[OE. <ets>glopnen</ets> to be frightened, frighten: cf. Icel.
<ets>gl⟦umac⟧pna</ets> to look downcast.]</ety> <def>To surprise or
astonish; to be startled or astonished.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

